%N A057681 a(n) = Sum_{j=0..floor(n/3)} (-1)^j*binomial(n,3*j).
%C A057681 Let M be any endomorphism on any vector space, such that M^3 = 1 (identity). Then (1-M)^n = a(n)-A057682(n)*M+z(n)*M^2, where z(0)=z(1)=0 and, apparently, z(n+2)=A057083(n). - _Stanislav Sykora_, Jun 10 2012
%C A057681 Pisano period lengths: 1, 3, 1, 6, 24, 3, 6, 12, 1, 24, 60, 6, 12, 6, 24, 24, 96, 3, 18, 24, ... . - _R. J. Mathar_, Aug 10 2012
%C A057681 {A057681, A057682, A*}, where A* is A057083 prefixed by two 0's, is the difference analog of the trigonometric functions of order 3, {k_1(x), k_2(x), k_3(x)}. For a definition see [Erdelyi] and the Shevelev link. - _Vladimir Shevelev_, Jun 25 2017
